    |<strong>{Glossary.*Permafrost Permafrost} temperatures have increased in most regions since the early 1980s (high confidence) although the rate of increase has varied regionally.
    |</strong> The temperature increase for colder permafrost was generally greater than for warmer permafrost (high confidence).
    |
    |See: <em>{Chapters.4.4_7.4_7_2 Section 4.7.2}, {'Table_4_8 Table 4.8}, {'Figure_4_24 Figure 4.24}
    |</em>

